import React from 'react';
import {Icon} from 'semantic-ui-react';

export default function HandleDropdown(props) {
  const dataValue = props.dataValue;
    switch (dataValue) {
    case 'Priority':
            return (<>
  <option value="Low"><Icon name='angle down'size='large'/>Low</option>
  <option value="Normal"><Icon name='blue angle up'size='large'/>Normal</option>
  <option value="High"> <Icon name='red angle double up'size='large'/>High</option>
  <option value="Safety"><Icon name='orange exclamation triangle'size='large'/>Safety</option> </>
)
    case 'Status':
           return (<>
  <option value="Raised"><Icon name='blue circle outline' size='large'/>Raised</option>
  <option value="Raised and Assigned"><Icon name='blue circle'size='large'/>Raised and Assigned</option>
  <option value="In Progress"><Icon name='orange circle'size='large'/>In Progress</option>
  <option value="On Hold"><Icon name='red circle'size='large'/>On Hold</option>
<option value="Completed"><Icon name='green circle' size='large'/>Completed</option> </>
)
    case 'Category':
           return (<>
  <option value="None">None</option>
  <option value="Equipment">Equipment</option>
  <option value="Paddock">Paddock</option>
  <option value="Fuel Tank">Fuel Tank</option>
  <option value="Silo">Silo</option>
<option value="Livestock">Livestock</option> </>
)
     case 'Asset':
            return <input name='blue circle'size='large'/>
    case 'Description':
           return <Icon name='red circle'size='large'/>
               
               default:
                return <Icon name='red circle'size='large'/>
        
}
}
